What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Safety Footwear Market?



Market Analysis and Size

Safety footwear can be defined as layering and protection footwear that is produced for specific purposes and protection against specific circumstances and elements. These categories of footwear have been reinforced and enhanced for rough and tough use. This footwear has been produced with specific materials that protect the wearer in many applications such as during mining, construction, and various other activities from many industries.

Some of the prime factors such as the rising concerns and awareness regarding worker and workplace safety along with stringent legislations, rising intensifying product usage across various industries, rising employment in industrial and utilities activities requiring protection and safety clothing and accessories, rising adoption of these inexpensive shoes, rising introduction of occupational safety standards and compliance with stiff regulations, and rising demand for safety shoes are expected to drive market growth. Moreover, the rising introduction of technologically advanced footwear, rising R&D activities, and increasing untapped geographical regions are further expected to create new opportunities for market growth in the forecast period.

However, the rising presence of fake and cheaper products that compromise on quality and assurance from various local players in the market is one of the major factors expected to restrain market growth in the forecast period.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the safety footwear market, which was USD 10.09 billion in 2022, would rocket up to USD 16.16 billion by 2030, and is expected to undergo a CAGR of 6.07% during the forecast period. “Leather” dominates the material segment of the market due to the appealing appearance of leather boots, the flexibility of leather material, and the quality that leather shoes offer.

